Hello Book Club Members,

Welcome to the July edition of our monthly newsletter! We’re excited to share updates and upcoming events for our community.

1. Featured Book of the Month
   Title: “The Silent Grove” by Clara Harrington
   Discussion Date: July 15, 2024 at 7:00 PM
   Location: Riverside Community Library, Meeting Room B

2. Author Q&A Session
   On July 20th at 6:30 PM, we’ll host Clara Harrington for a virtual Q&A. Submit your questions by July 12th via our online form.

3. Summer Reading Challenge
   Track your progress from June 1st through August 31st. Members who read five books earn a special enamel bookmark. Log your books on our website.

4. Volunteer Opportunities
   We need help organizing our annual book drive in September. If you can spare a few hours, please reply to this email or sign up on the volunteer page.

5. Member Spotlight
   Congratulations to Maria Santos for her book review of “Turning Tides”! Her thoughtful analysis earned top marks from fellow readers.

Thank you for being part of our vibrant reading community. As always, feel free to reach out with suggestions or feedback.

Happy reading!
– Alice and the Book Club Committee